Testing:
    - As a Developer we must test the applications before moving to
      Production Environment.

    - In General Testing Divided into two Categories.

        1. Manual Testing

        2. Automation Testing

    - Now a days all projects using Automation Testing while Testing the
      Application.

    - Automation Testing Classified into 3 categories.
        1. Unit Testing
        2. Integration Testing
        3. End To End Testing

Unit Testing:

    - Checking the Perticular Functionality with dummy scenarioes
      called as Unit Testing.


Integration Testing:

    - Testing the Perticular Functionality with Actual Scenarioes
      called as Integration Testing.

End to End Testing:

    - Testing the Application with Different States(End Point States)
      called as e2e testing.



- we can write the Test Cases by using karma.


Installation of karma
---------------------
>npm install -g karma


Testing the Controller:
-----------------------

var app = angular.module("app",[]);

app.controller("ctrl",ctrl);
function ctrl($scope){
    $scope.title = "Hello";
}


karma.conf.js
-------------
describe("testing ctrl",function(){
  var $controller;
  inject("test case one",function(_$controller_){
        module("app");
        $controller = _$controller_;
  };
});

it("first test case",function(){
    var result = $controller.get("ctrl",{$scope});
    expect(result).equlasTo("Hello");
});

> start karma



Testing Services:
-----------------

var app = angular.module("app",[]);
app.service("my_service",my_service);
function my_service(){
    this.getData = function(){
        return ["AngularJS","Angular4","NodeJS","MongoDB"];
    }
}


karma.conf.js
-------------
describe("testing service",function(){
    var testService;
    @injector(function(){

    });
});



















